item.title: Help! ive done everythink on the server tutorial but still cant get my server up
item.dc:creator: @sitebanis sitebanis
item.description:
@sitebanis wrote:

Open up the Command Prompt (cmd) and type in the command ‘ipconfig’. The ‘Default Gateway’ is your router’s IP address. The ‘IP Address’ is your local computer’s IP address. The address that you see at http://ipchicken.com is your external IP address. now go to the adress bar on the internet window and type in your router’s IP address. (with no “www” or " .com ")[br][size=1]Posted on: April 01, 2007, 07:59:05 PM[/size][hr]the command propt is in start > all programs > accsessories > command prompt.
